Question 1

Which of the following are valid for representing the expression <t> Alan and Mairi. dreamed.? Select all that apply.

A. <t> Alan + Mairi . </t>
✔ B. <t> Alan + Mairi + dreamed . </t>
✔ C. <term> Alan + Mairi + dreamed . </term>
D. <term> Alan + Mairi + to dream . </term>
✔ E. <t> Alan + Mairi + to dream . </t>
F. <term> Alan + Mairi + to dream . </term>
G. <t> Alan </t>

Question 2

An XML document has a tree structure. It:

A. can have multiple roots and multiple leaves
B. can have multiple roots or records
✔ C. must have a single root.
D. must have a single leaf.

Question 3

What is the requirement of a well-formed XML document? Select all that apply.

✔ A. There is a single root element.
✔ B. Each element is properly nested between an opening and a closing tag.
C. There are no unexpected tags
D. The tags must come from the set pre-defined by W3C.
E. White space is not allowed in Text Content parts.

Question 4

To create an XML document using XmlTextWriter class, you need to open a FileStream and then create an XmlTextWriter object:

fs = new FileStream("c:\\book.xml", FileMode.CreateNew);
XmlTextWriter xtw = new XmlTextWriter(fs);
System.Text.Encoding enc = null;

What operation must be performed in order to properly format the XML file?

✔ A. xtw.WriteStartDocument()
B. xtw.Close()
C. xtw.WriteEndDocument()
D. xtw.WriteAttributeString()

Question 5

You are given the piece of code below:

(1) XmlTextReader reader = new XmlTextReader("a.xml");
(2) while (reader.Read())
(3) {
(4)     if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.Element &&
(5)         reader.Name == "book")
(6)     {
(7)         Console.WriteLine(reader.GetAttribute("title"));
(8)     }
(9) }


Answer the following questions:

(1) Will this piece of code create an in-memory tree to store
the entire content of the XML file? True or False?
✔ Answer 1: No

(2) What line of code in the file (number) is the only line that loads a node into memory?
✔ Answer 2: Line 5

(3) If this code has to call method reader.MoveToAttribute("author")
after Read(), must the node have attributes? True or False?
✔ Answer 3: False

Question 6

An XPath expression allows to have a function call at the end of the expression.

A. True
✔ B. False

Question 7

What is the XML processing model that reads one node into memory a time based on the given path expression?

A. DOM (Document Object Model)
✔ B. SAX (Simple API for XML)
C. XmlDocument
D. X-path

